<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="122" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7">
  <metadata>
    <title>Audit document create profile — reproduce failure, categorize, recommend restoration vs remediation</title>
    <phase>Wave 12 — MVP Completion</phase>
    <wave>12</wave>
    <sub-wave>12.1</sub-wave>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Read-only audit; no code modification; output is a notes doc</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>W12-1-Audit</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <tags>audit, bff-api, wizard, playbook, document, investigation, wave12</tags>
    <estimated-effort>~half day</estimated-effort>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
The document create profile feature is currently broken but was previously working. Audit it: locate the code, reproduce the failure, categorize the root cause (R7 regression vs inherent playbook engine bug class), and recommend restoration vs remediation with effort estimates per path.
  </prompt>

  <role>
You are a code auditor doing read-only investigation. Do NOT modify code. Do NOT run deployments. Your job is to produce a concrete audit that enables Wave 12.3 task generation with a disposition (restore vs remediate) and realistic effort estimate.
  </role>

  <goal>
Output a notes doc at projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/audits/wave12-122-document-create-profile.md containing: (1) location of all code involved (BFF endpoint + playbook definition + UI invocation point), (2) reproduced failure with diagnostic detail, (3) root-cause categorization, (4) disposition recommendation (restore or remediate) with effort estimate. Pay special attention to the structured-output field mapping into the document profile form (this likely parallels the Prefill wizard pattern in task 123).
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    - Operator-reported state: feature was previously working; currently broken
    - "Document create profile" likely: user uploads/selects document → LLM extracts metadata fields → fields prefill into document profile form → user reviews/saves
    - Likely architecture: Start → AiCompletion (with structured output schema matching profile fields) → ReturnResponse → wizard UI binds output to form fields
    - May share Action output schema pattern with the three Prefill wizards in task 123
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    - Read-only. No code edits. No deploys. No Dataverse writes.
    - Investigate only — do NOT propose code fixes inside this task. Wave 12.3 POMLs handle that.
    - Cite file:line references for every claim.
    - If this feature shares Action output schema pattern with task 123's three Prefill wizards, note that — but conduct audit independently.
    - Sub-Agent Write Boundary: writes go ONLY to projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/audits/.
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      - projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/wave12-mvp-completion-plan.md (§2.2 Wizards)
      - projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md
      - projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/handoffs/wave11-t116-narrate-systematic-assessment.md
      - projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/spikes/poc-vs-playbook-engine-architecture.md
      - .claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <relevant-files>
      - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/** (BFF endpoint — search "document" / "profile" / "create")
      - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookOrchestrationService.cs
      - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PublicContracts/InvokePlaybookAi.cs
      - src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/** (wizard UI may be here)
      - src/client/code-pages/** (wizard UI alternate location)
      - src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/** (document profile form may live here)
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <steps>
1. **Locate feature code** (30 min):
   - Search BFF endpoints for "document-create-profile" / "create-profile" / "profile" / similar
   - Search code pages / SpaarkeAi for wizard UI invocation + profile form
   - Identify playbook (sprk_analysisplaybook row + consumer-type)
   - Document: BFF endpoint file:line, UI entry point file:line, playbook ID + node count, profile form component file:line

2. **Inspect playbook shape AND Action output schema** (30 min):
   - Query playbook + nodes via mcp__dataverse__read_query
   - Document node count, executor types, fan-out / iteration presence
   - **Critical**: locate Action (sprk_analysisaction) used by AiCompletion node and inspect `sprk_outputschemajson` — defines structured output mapping to profile form fields
   - Document output schema field set + intended binding to profile form

3. **Determine if profile form is schema-driven or hardcoded** (20 min):
   - Read wizard UI component
   - Look for: dynamic field rendering from schema OR hardcoded field-name-to-form-field mapping
   - Determines what "preserving the contract" looks like

4. **Trace data flow end-to-end** (30 min):
   - Walk: UI uploads doc → BFF endpoint → IInvokePlaybookAi → orchestrator → AiCompletion call to OpenAI with structured schema → response → UI binds to form
   - Identify where regression OR engine bug class surfaces
   - Specifically check: does playbook use /narrate's failure-prone features (fan-out, LoadKnowledge passthrough, multi-field ReturnResponse composition)?

5. **Reproduce failure if possible** (30 min):
   - If deployed environment accessible: run wizard with sample document
   - If not: trace expected vs actual
   - Document failure symptom + evidence

6. **Categorize root cause** (15 min):
   - **R7 regression**: enum rename / DI / dispatch broke reference → cheap restoration
   - **Inherent engine bug class** → thin code wrapper remediation, ~50-100 LOC, preserves Action output schema
   - **Configuration drift** (Dataverse row data wrong) → data fix
   - **Schema/UI mismatch** (output schema doesn't match UI expects) → schema OR UI fix

7. **Produce disposition recommendation** (20 min):
   - Per-disposition effort estimate
   - If remediation: sketch what code-defined wrapper looks like — should be very thin (load Action by code, call IOpenAiClient.GetStructuredCompletionRawAsync, return LLM's structured output; ~50-100 LOC)
   - Flag whether work can be shared with task 123's three Prefill wizards (likely yes if all follow Action-output-schema-as-contract pattern)

8. **Write notes doc** at projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/audits/wave12-122-document-create-profile.md (30 min)

  </steps>

  <tools>
    - Read (file inspection)
    - Grep / Glob (code search)
    - Bash (dotnet test if useful; curl smoke)
    - mcp__dataverse__describe / mcp__dataverse__read_query (playbook + Action inspection)
    - Write (notes doc only)
    - TodoWrite (track audit progress)
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    - notes/audits/wave12-122-document-create-profile.md
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    - [ ] BFF endpoint + UI entry point + playbook ID + profile form component located with file:line references
    - [ ] Playbook shape + Action output schema documented (field set listed)
    - [ ] Profile form binding pattern determined (schema-driven vs hardcoded)
    - [ ] Failure reproduced OR walked through with predicted-failure-point
    - [ ] Root cause categorized
    - [ ] Disposition recommended with effort estimate; remediation sketch if applicable
    - [ ] Note whether work can be shared with task 123's three Prefill wizards
    - [ ] notes/audits/wave12-122-document-create-profile.md exists with file:line references throughout
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
